---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header.astro'
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro'

const toc = [
  { id: 'collect', label: 'Information we collect' },
  { id: 'use', label: 'How we use information' },
  { id: 'storage', label: 'Data storage & security' },
  { id: 'rights', label: 'Your rights' },
  { id: 'retention', label: 'Data retention' },
  { id: 'third', label: 'Third-party services' },
  { id: 'changes', label: 'Changes to this policy' },
  { id: 'contact', label: 'Contact' },
]
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy"
  description="Union's privacy policy: what we collect, how we use it, your rights."
>
  <Header back />

  <section class="title-block">
    <div>
      <div class="eyebrow">Privacy policy</div>
      <h1>Privacy, <em>plainly.</em></h1>
    </div>
    <dl class="meta">
      <dt>Last updated</dt>
      <dd>May 2026</dd>
      <dt>Questions</dt>
      <dd><a href="mailto:privacy@unionwith.app">privacy@unionwith.app</a></dd>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <main class="doc">
    <aside class="toc" aria-label="Contents">
      <div class="lbl">Contents</div>
      <ol>
        {toc.map((t) => <li><a href={`#${t.id}`}>{t.label}</a></li>)}
      </ol>
    </aside>

    <article class="prose">
      <p class="lede">
        At Union, we care about your privacy and aim to keep data collection
        simple, transparent, and minimal. This policy explains what information
        we collect, how we use it, and your choices when using the Union app
        and related services.
      </p>

      <h2 id="collect">
        <span class="h-num">§ 01</span>Information we <em>collect</em>
      </h2>

      <h3>Account information</h3>
      <p>When you create an account, we may collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your email address</li>
        <li>Authentication information used to sign you in securely</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Usage information</h3>
      <p>
        We may collect limited information about how you use the app,
        including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>App interactions and feature usage</li>
        <li>Device type and app version</li>
        <li>Diagnostic and crash information</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Content you create</h3>
      <p>
        If you use journaling, prayer, reflections, notes, or other personal
        features within Union, the content you create may be stored securely to
        provide the service to you.
      </p>

      <h3>Religious content &amp; special-category data</h3>
      <p>
        Some of what you share with Union — your check-ins and your journal
        entries, including any voice journal you record — can reveal your
        religious beliefs. Under UK GDPR (Article 9), that is special-category
        personal data, and we treat it with particular care.
      </p>
      <p>
        We process this content only to provide the service to you: matching
        prayers and verses to the moment, and keeping your own reflections for
        you to return to. We do this on the basis of your explicit consent. We
        never sell it, and we never share it with other people or with
        third parties for their own purposes. When you delete your account, this
        content is deleted along with it, straight away and without a grace
        period.
      </p>

      <h2 id="use">
        <span class="h-num">§ 02</span>How we <em>use</em> information
      </h2>
      <p>We use information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide and improve the app</li>
        <li>Authenticate and secure your account</li>
        <li>Personalise your experience</li>
        <li>Maintain app performance and reliability</li>
        <li>Respond to support requests</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="tagline">We do not sell your personal information.</p>

      <h2 id="storage">
        <span class="h-num">§ 03</span>Data storage &amp; <em>security</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect
        your information from unauthorised access, loss, misuse, or disclosure.
      </p>
      <p>
        No online service can guarantee absolute security, but we work to keep
        your data protected and secure.
      </p>

      <h2 id="rights">
        <span class="h-num">§ 04</span>Your <em>rights</em>
      </h2>
      <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access your personal data</li>
        <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent where applicable</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To make a privacy request, contact us at <a
          class="inline"
          href="mailto:privacy@unionwith.app">privacy@unionwith.app</a
        >.
      </p>

      <h2 id="retention">
        <span class="h-num">§ 05</span>Data <em>retention</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        We retain information only for as long as necessary to provide the
        Services, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce
        our agreements.
      </p>

      <h2 id="third">
        <span class="h-num">§ 06</span>Third-party <em>services</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        We use trusted service providers to help operate, maintain, and improve
        Union. These providers only process information necessary to provide
        their services to us.
      </p>

      <h2 id="changes">
        <span class="h-num">§ 07</span>Changes to this <em>policy</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make
        material changes, we will update the “Last updated” date at the top of
        the page.
      </p>

      <h2 id="contact">
        <span class="h-num">§ 08</span><em>Contact</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, write
        to <a class="inline" href="mailto:privacy@unionwith.app"
          >privacy@unionwith.app</a
        >.
      </p>

      <div class="ornament" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="line"></div>
        <span class="mark">&#10086;</span>
        <div class="line"></div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
